# AGENTS process (default — no reminder needed)

Treat **every** coding task that changes `api/`, `web/`, Docker, or migrations as requiring the **full** workflow in **[`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)**. The user should **not** have to type “follow the process” — you run the deploy/verify steps yourself.

## Do by default (unless AGENTS.md says to skip)

1. **Deploy** — you run Compose yourself; commands, when to skip, stale-image **`dev-fresh`**: **[`local-docker-deploy.mdc`](local-docker-deploy.mdc)** (**`make dev-fast`** preferred; **`make dev`** for shipped-image parity). Skip for **docs-only** / **comment-only** with zero build/runtime effect.
2. **Verify + base URL** — health / **`docker compose ps`** / exact **`http://localhost…`** for the stack you used: **[`local-docker-deploy.mdc`](local-docker-deploy.mdc)** § *End-of-task* / *Tell the user where to click*.
3. **`CHANGELOG.md`** — **[`changelog.mdc`](changelog.mdc)** (skip rules when no ship impact).
4. **`docs/USER_GUIDE.md`** — **[`user-documentation.mdc`](user-documentation.mdc)** when operator-visible UX changes (same change when practical).
5. **`git commit`** — **[`git-commits.mdc`](git-commits.mdc)**; do not leave a large uncommitted diff unless the user asked to hold commits.

## What not to do

- Do not end with “you should run **`make dev-fast`**” or “**`make dev`**” as the only action when you can run commands.
- Do not skip changelog because the user did not mention release notes.
- Do not assume hot reload under **`make dev`** — see **[`local-docker-deploy.mdc`](local-docker-deploy.mdc)** § *Why “changes aren’t live”*.

## Canonical doc

**[`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)** § *Development process* and *Local testing*. **Logging:** **[`logging.mdc`](logging.mdc)** / **`docs/LOGGING.md`**. Human **Git** narrative: **`docs/DEVELOPMENT.md`** § *Git commits* (detail lives in **`git-commits.mdc`**).
